There has been a large body of research on the role of social capital in online conversations .
 For example, @cite studied the relationship between social capital and political polarization in Twitter and found that users with similar political views tend to cluster along a common ideological dimension based on who they follow .
 In addition, researchers have also studied the effect of directed communication on social capital .
 In the context of online social networks, researchers focused on the use of social networking sites to improve the quality of online conversations, e .
g .
, Twitter and Facebook .
 In this paper, we focus on the problem of designing a conversational avatar capable of facilitating casual conversations with older users .

